---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import business from '../data/business.json';
---

<Base
  title="Our Story | Ottawa Mattress, Beaumont Collection"
  description="Ottawa Luxury Mattress is built on decades of upholstery craft and a belief that handcrafted quality doesn't have to cost three times what it should. Learn who we are and why we build what we build."
>

  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Our Story</h1>
      <p>We're not a mattress chain. We're craftspeople who figured out how to do this better.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--white">
    <div class="container story-body">

      <div class="story-section">
        <h2>Kessels Upholstery, Ottawa</h2>
        <p>
          Ottawa Luxury Mattress is an extension of Kessels Upholstery, a long-standing
          upholstery and furniture operation at 107 Colonnade Rd S in Nepean. We know
          how things are built. We know what quality materials feel like and how long
          they actually last. That background is what makes us different from a retail
          mattress store.
        </p>
        <p>
          We're not a franchise. We don't carry a catalog. We look at what people actually
          need, source the right materials, and have it built properly.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-section">
        <h2>The Mennonite builders</h2>
        <p>
          Every Beaumont mattress is handcrafted by Mennonite artisans in South Ontario.
          These are families who have been building furniture and mattresses for generations.
          No assembly line. No robotics. No shortcuts in materials.
        </p>
        <p>
          We work directly with our builders. We specify every detail of every mattress:
          the latex ILD, the ticking fabric, the tufting pattern, the zipper placement.
          They execute it. We stand behind it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-section">
        <h2>Why natural latex</h2>
        <p>
          Memory foam became dominant in the mattress industry because it's cheap to produce
          and easy to market. "Conforms to your body" sounds great until the foam has
          compressed 40% and your mattress is five years old.
        </p>
        <p>
          Natural latex doesn't work that way. It's harvested from rubber trees, processed
          into a resilient foam, and it genuinely lasts 25 years or more. It doesn't
          compress under weight the way synthetic foam does. It's naturally hypoallergenic
          and antimicrobial. It doesn't off-gas. It sleeps cooler because it's actually breathable.
        </p>
        <p>
          The only reason natural latex mattresses are expensive is that the major brands
          have built enormous markup chains between the material and the consumer. We haven't.
          We go direct.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-section">
        <h2>The pricing</h2>
        <p>
          A Beaumont mattress starts at $1,200 CAD and goes to $6,000 depending on size
          and specification. A comparable custom build from Hästens or Vi Spring would run
          $8,000 to $20,000+. A Saatva "luxury" latex mattress is $2,000+ for a product
          you have no hand in specifying.
        </p>
        <p>
          We're not trying to be the cheapest mattress in Ottawa. We're trying to be the
          best value for someone who wants a real, lasting mattress built to their needs.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--navy text-center">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 580px;">
      <h2>Come see for yourself</h2>
      <p style="opacity: 0.82; margin: 1rem 0 2rem; line-height: 1.75;">
        We have mattresses in the showroom. Come in, lie on one, ask us anything.
        No appointment needed during business hours.
      </p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-outline-cream">Visit the Showroom</a>
        <a href={`tel:${business.phone}`} class="btn btn-outline-cream">{business.phoneFormatted}</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>

<style>
  .story-body {
    max-width: 720px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 3.5rem;
  }

  .story-section h2 {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .story-section p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    line-height: 1.78;
  }

  .story-section p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
</style>
